    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but you said \"the real deal is\" that they create a cycle of recidivism. that sounds like you're saying the systemic bias side is the actual reality of it. can't you just look at the stats on crime rates dropping in certain areas when policing goes up? isnt that a valid way to measure if it's working?",
